 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P03-T016 (Factsheet schema + deterministic extraction)
+
+- Sixteenth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the first of S1-P03 (Factsheet, 人话版, quality gate), one task per run. Goal: extract stable facts before generating any text. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; a read-only D1 sample of 200 items (changed_db=False), no worker/D1 change. Owner directive 2026-07-16: the S1-P03 human baseline is a machine baseline marked provisional_machine, pending Owner spot-check (no fabricated human labels). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: schemas/factsheet.schema.json (common fields title/url/date/authors/doi/categories each value-or-null, plus board_ext doc_number/agency/venue/units and p0_present), tools/extract_factsheet.py (deterministic date/DOI/文号/单位/authors extractors, missing -> null), and factsheet_baseline_200.json (a 200-sample provisional machine baseline). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P03-T016/test-results/factsheet_tests.txt): every field is value-or-null (missing published_at -> date null, absent 文号 -> doc_number null, never fabricated); the 200-sample schema validation PASSES; the extraction is deterministic (a re-extract is byte-identical); and the P0 fields have a baseline across all 200 -- title/url/date at 100% coverage per board, with board2 DOI 60/86 and board3 doc_number 2/85 (board3 is currently media, not policy documents, consistent with DRIFT-FACT-006). This is the fact layer for T017 (defect baseline) and T018 (L0-L3 人话版 + evidence locator) and the governance precondition for FACT-002. Cost (unknown != 0): 1 read-only D1 SELECT, D1 rows_read about 200, D1 written 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P02-T015 (Source Drift CI; S1-P02 complete)
 
 - Fifteenth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the last of S1-P02 (Source Registry single source truth), one task per run. Goal: block a new hand-written source array, UI label drift, and D1/runtime sources not registered in the Registry. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; a read-only repo scan, no worker/D1 change. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/check_source_drift.py (repo scanner allowing exactly one approved source array; runtime/D1 comparison of the worker source-id set vs compiled/runtime.json; UI label drift via ui_labels.registry_hash == compiled registry_hash) and SOURCE_DRIFT_EXCEPTIONS.yaml (approved: the worker REGISTRY is the single source array; no unregistered ids). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P02-T015/test-results/drift_ci_tests.txt): the real worker PASSES with no false positive (one approved array, worker 33 == runtime 33, ui hash matches); injecting a second source array REGISTRY2 with an unregistered id rogue-src makes CI DRIFT (flags both the unapproved array and the live-not-registered id); mutating ui_labels.registry_hash makes CI DRIFT (labels not regenerated from the current registry); and restoring returns PASS. This completes S1-P02: schema (T012) -> migration (T013) -> deterministic compiler (T014) -> drift CI (T015), so DRIFT-FACT-006-class source drift cannot silently return. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0 (repo scan), R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
